http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Music History Curriculum Standards for grades 9-12.
Singing - Students will sing, alone and with others, a varied repertoire of music.
Demonstrate an understanding of elements of music by singing/chanting.
Playing Instruments - Students will perform on instruments alone and with others a varied repertoire of music.
Demonstrate an understanding of elements of music by playing on instruments.
Improvising - Students will improvise melodies, variations, and accompaniments.
Demonstrate an understanding of elements of music, genres, and/or style periods through improvisation.
Improvise, alone or with others, a short melodic, rhythmic, or harmonic passage to demonstrate a given emotion.
Composing - Students will compose and arrange music within specified guidelines.
an understanding of elements of music, genres, and/or style periods through composition.
Demonstrate an understanding of elements of music and/or style periods by arranging.
Reading and Notating - Students will read and notate music.
Demonstrate basic reading skills using standard and/or non-standard notation.
Demonstrate basic notating skills using standard and/or non-standard notation.
Listening and Analyzing - Students will listen to, analyze and describe music.
Listen and describe music of various style periods and vocal (including opera and musical theater) and instrumental genres.
Analyze and describe music of various style periods and vocal and instrumental genres.
Evaluating - Students will evaluate music and music performances.
Evaluate musical works using elements of music characteristic to each style period.
Evaluate musical performances using elements of music characteristic to each style period.
Interdisciplinary Connections - Students will understand relationships between music, the other arts, and disciplines outside the arts.
Demonstrate an understanding of how the elements of music change from one style period to another.
Demonstrate an understanding of the connection of elements (e.g., color, balance, texture) between music and the other arts disciplines.
Demonstrate an understanding of the connections between music and disciplines outside the arts.
Demonstrate an understanding of becoming a responsible consumer of music.
Historical and Cultural Relationships - Students will understand music in relation to history and culture.
Explore the reciprocal relationship between music and the influences of history and culture.
